ivardefs.name: dataRequirement_
ivardefs.desc: If the evaluation could not be completed due to lack of information, or additional information would potentially result in a more accurate response, this element will a description of the data required in order to proceed with the evaluation. A subsequent

ivardefs.name: encounter
ivardefs.desc: The encounter during which this response was created or to which the creation of this record is tightly associated.

ivardefs.name: evaluationMessage_
ivardefs.desc: Messages resulting from the evaluation of the artifact or artifacts. As part of evaluating the request, the engine may produce informational or warning messages. These messages will be provided by this element.

ivardefs.name: identifier_
ivardefs.desc: Allows a service to provide  unique, business identifiers for the response.

ivardefs.name: note_
ivardefs.desc: Provides a mechanism to communicate additional information about the response.

ivardefs.name: occurrenceDateTime
ivardefs.desc: Indicates when the guidance response was processed.

ivardefs.name: outputParameters
ivardefs.desc: The output parameters of the evaluation, if any. Many modules will result in the return of specific resources such as procedure or communication requests that are returned as part of the operation result. However, modules may define specific outputs that

ivardefs.name: performer
ivardefs.desc: Provides a reference to the device that performed the guidance.

ivardefs.name: reasonCode_
ivardefs.desc: Describes the reason for the guidance response in coded or textual form.

ivardefs.name: reasonReference_
ivardefs.desc: Indicates the reason the request was initiated. This is typically provided as a parameter to the evaluation and echoed by the service, although for some use cases, such as subscription- or event-based scenarios, it may provide an indication of the cause f

ivardefs.name: requestIdentifier
ivardefs.desc: The identifier of the request associated with this response. If an identifier was given as part of the request, it will be reproduced here to enable the requester to more easily identify the response in a multi-request scenario.

ivardefs.name: result
ivardefs.desc: The actions, if any, produced by the evaluation of the artifact.

ivardefs.name: status
ivardefs.desc: The status of the response. If the evaluation is completed successfully, the status will indicate success. However, in order to complete the evaluation, the engine may require more information. In this case, the status will be data-required, and the respo

ivardefs.name: subject
ivardefs.desc: The patient for which the request was processed.

properties.desc: A guidance response is the formal response to a guidance request, including any output parameters returned by the evaluation, as well as the description of any proposed actions to be taken.
